org.apache.spark.sql.sources.v2.writer

Interface WriterCommitMessage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @InterfaceStability.Evolving
public interface WriterCommitMessage
extends java.io.Serializable
    A commit message returned by DataWriter.commit() and will be sent back to the driver side as the input parameter of DataSourceWriter.commit(WriterCommitMessage[]). This is an empty interface, data sources should define their own message class and use it in their DataWriter.commit() and DataSourceWriter.commit(WriterCommitMessage[]) implementations.
